<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 06 at 3:05PM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Very Cold Wind Chills Late This Afternoon...
Temperatures in the lower single digits combined with winds
around 20 to 25 MPH will lead to wind chill values around 15 to 20
degrees below zero over the next few hours. A wind chill advisory
is in effect for the area beginning at 600 PM, when values are
expected to drop below 20 degrees below zero as the sun sets.
Be sure to bundle up, covering exposed skin, as frostbite can
still happen within a half hour of exposure.</description>
